                       # advantage and disadvantage of udp ip 

        ğŸ”¹ UDP (User Datagram Protocol) Advantages âœ…
Lightweight / Low Overhead

UDP header is only 8 bytes â†’ fast transmission.
Faster than TCP

No connection setup (3-way handshake)
No retransmissions â†’ suitable for real-time apps.
Supports Broadcasting / Multicasting

Can send packets to multiple hosts at once.
Simple

Easy to implement
Good for small query-response protocols (DNS, DHCP)

ğŸ”¹ UDP Disadvantages âŒ
Unreliable

No guarantee that data reaches the destination.
No Ordering

Packets may arrive out of order.
No Flow Control / Congestion Control

Sender can overwhelm receiver â†’ packet loss possible.
Error Handling Minimal

Only optional checksum â†’ errors may go undetected



